  "texts": [
    "This means that the astrometric solution for KiDZ and KiDS are nominally different, at the level of existing systematic differences between Gaia and SDSS or 2MASS.",
    "Figure 11 shows the residual difference between the astrometric solutions of KiDS stars (i.e.",
    "calibrated with Gaia) with respect to SDSS stars, demonstrating that there is no significant systematic bias in the two astrometric systems.",
    "As such, we conclude that there is unlikely to be any significant systematic effect imprinted on the KiDZ data through the use of a different astrometric basis in the THELI-Phot pipeline.",
    "A170, page 9 of 54 Fig. 10."
  ]
}